Alexander Razuvaev, Director of the analytical department "Alpari"
In the 1990s, inflation sometimes reached 20-30% per month, at zero it was also above the current level, another fact that it was then offset by rapid economic growth.
I think by the end of the year inflation will be 8-8.5%.
Platon Maguta, Managing Assets of the Maguta Foundation
