China's largest companies have joined forces against Alibaba
Chinese companies, including China’s largest commercial real estate developer Dalian Wanda Group and internet giant Tencent Holdings (society, messenger, etc.) and Baidu (China’s largest search engine), are creating a company that will compete in the online market with Alibaba.
However, to achieve the miracle of the Chinese Internet, which has left behind even its American rivals - eBay and Amazon.com, will not be easy.
Union of the largest
The companies plan to invest 5 billion yuan ($814 million) in the joint venture, 70% of which will be owned by Wanda and 15% by each of the Internet companies, the Wanda Group said in a statement.
