But he believes that the new company will hardly be able to seriously compete with Alibaba immediately after its creation: “Rome cannot be built in one day”.
The fact that Alibaba is not so easy to compete with not only new companies, but also the well-deserved leaders of the world’s online commerce, shows a report published yesterday on Alibaba’s financial performance for the last quarter.
Alibaba is often described as something on average between eBay and Amazon.com, but from April to June, the Chinese company earned more than both of its American competitors combined.
Alibaba’s net profit for the period is almost twice as high as its competitors’ aggregated index – it has grown nearly three times in the year and amounted to $1.99 billion.
“Alibaba still has a huge potential to generate money, largely thanks to its mobile apps,” said Bloomberg in a statement from the Hong Kong-based Arete Research Service.
According to Alibaba’s updated prospectus on the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission’s website, the number of active mobile users of the company’s services in July was 188 million, which is significantly above the March figure (163 million people).
At the same time, 32.8% of all Alibaba’s transactions for the past quarter went to mobile devices.
